The paper deals with the problem of searching in partially ordered structures, specifically tree-like partial orders. This falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.AI). The problem also involves minimizing costs, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the problem involves identifying vertices in a tree, which is related to computational geometry (cs.CG).
